The paper deals with motion planning for autonomous driving, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The focus is on achieving optimal performance, which involves decision-making and control, making it relevant to systems and control (cs.SY). The use of a search-based approach and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the evaluation of the algorithm's performance on a simulated track with different curvatures suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be relevant.
